AUDIENCE: So, what is Google
doing with all this data?

00:40:59.260 --> 00:41:00.920
What are you ulterior
motives here?

00:41:03.600 --> 00:41:07.800
BRANDON BADGER: This is the
classified talk, right?

00:41:07.800 --> 00:41:11.000
Honestly, it's to build a fun
experience and a fun game.

00:41:13.660 --> 00:41:15.860
I know there's been speculation,
oh, Google could

00:41:15.860 --> 00:41:18.100
use this data to improve maps,
and maybe that's the case, but

00:41:18.100 --> 00:41:21.850
we haven't even thought
about that, honestly.

00:41:21.850 --> 00:41:24.760
I think we're taking the
approach, can we build a new

00:41:24.760 --> 00:41:26.070
type of gaming experience?

00:41:26.070 --> 00:41:28.340
Some of it is to showcase
the technology.

00:41:28.340 --> 00:41:30.740
So something like Google Glass,
there's definitely a

00:41:30.740 --> 00:41:34.900
good synergy with these types of
games and Nexus phones and

00:41:34.900 --> 00:41:37.460
different types of technology.

00:41:37.460 --> 00:41:39.870
I think that's more
what drives it.

00:41:39.870 --> 00:41:41.120
Go ahead.

