00:41:56.600 --> 00:41:59.220
And then also, have
you figured out--

00:41:59.220 --> 00:42:00.260
BRANDON BADGER: We just
use fake money.

00:42:00.260 --> 00:42:03.400
AUDIENCE: No, I mean, but you
get your services for free, I

00:42:03.400 --> 00:42:04.360
would suspect.

00:42:04.360 --> 00:42:06.340
I'm just wondering if you've
figured out what the run rate

00:42:06.340 --> 00:42:08.020
would be if you were
an outside company.

00:42:08.020 --> 00:42:08.670
BRANDON BADGER: I don't know.

00:42:08.670 --> 00:42:11.080
AUDIENCE: And then also, how
have you thought about how you

00:42:11.080 --> 00:42:15.690
would monetize the game if
you decided to do that?

00:42:15.690 --> 00:42:17.680
BRANDON BADGER: We're still
focused on building a great,

00:42:17.680 --> 00:42:20.460
fun game and growing
the user base.

00:42:20.460 --> 00:42:22.900
We're confident that if you
build a game like this, that

00:42:22.900 --> 00:42:26.080
we can come up with ways
to monetize it.

00:42:26.080 --> 00:42:28.870
So as I mentioned earlier, it
might be charging for the

00:42:28.870 --> 00:42:30.100
game, it might be subscriptions,
but we're

00:42:30.100 --> 00:42:32.580
really trying to avoid that and
we're trying to keep the

00:42:32.580 --> 00:42:36.180
game free because we're Google
and we come to things from

00:42:36.180 --> 00:42:38.580
more of an advertising
point of view.

00:42:38.580 --> 00:42:42.210
So we've been doing some
partnerships with some local

00:42:42.210 --> 00:42:44.020
businesses like Jamba Juice.

00:42:44.020 --> 00:42:47.330
We think there's something
powerful in helping influence

00:42:47.330 --> 00:42:50.980
and encouraging people to go
to a retail location, so we

00:42:50.980 --> 00:42:53.860
made the Jamba Juices, we did
an experiment where we made

00:42:53.860 --> 00:42:56.090
them portals in the game,
and so we're still

00:42:56.090 --> 00:42:57.190
collecting data from that.

00:42:57.190 --> 00:43:02.220
We've done a partnership with
Hint bottled water where

00:43:02.220 --> 00:43:05.750
there's power codes underneath
the bottle caps that you can

00:43:05.750 --> 00:43:08.940
type into your Ingress
app to get power ups.

00:43:08.940 --> 00:43:10.320
So I think maybe that's
a way to do it.

00:43:10.320 --> 00:43:14.770
But to be honest, we're still
brainstorming what the

00:43:14.770 --> 00:43:16.020
business models might be.

