00:43:37.420 --> 00:43:41.050
I've got one in my bag, too.

00:43:41.050 --> 00:43:45.280
AUDIENCE: Actually, two
questions I had were answered

00:43:45.280 --> 00:43:50.650
already, but any plans for
above Level Eight?

00:43:50.650 --> 00:43:53.420
BRANDON BADGER: We're
thinking about it.

00:43:53.420 --> 00:43:55.280
We're thinking about different
types of missions and

00:43:55.280 --> 00:43:55.950
achievements and things.

00:43:55.950 --> 00:43:58.850
I mean, it's sort of a rat
race where we could do 16

00:43:58.850 --> 00:44:00.200
levels and then 32 levels.

00:44:00.200 --> 00:44:01.420
I think you could just
keep doing that.

00:44:01.420 --> 00:44:05.110
So we're trying to think of
other ways where we can build

00:44:05.110 --> 00:44:08.290
enough head room where you
feel like there's a

00:44:08.290 --> 00:44:12.120
progression there, but we're
still debating how far we want

00:44:12.120 --> 00:44:16.240
to take it with just leveling
up on the point.

00:44:16.240 --> 00:44:17.500
We're still figuring it out.

00:44:17.500 --> 00:44:17.850
AUDIENCE: Cheers.

00:44:17.850 --> 00:44:20.772
Thanks.

00:44:20.772 --> 00:44:23.560
AUDIENCE: So I think one of the
hardest things to scale is

00:44:23.560 --> 00:44:24.980
the human aspect of the game.

00:44:24.980 --> 00:44:26.695
So you mentioned that you have
a team of people that's

00:44:26.695 --> 00:44:28.410
approving portals.

00:44:28.410 --> 00:44:30.660
What's a good strategy
of scaling that?

00:44:30.660 --> 00:44:32.790
And I guess the second question
is, how long does

00:44:32.790 --> 00:44:34.100
typically a portal get approved

00:44:34.100 --> 00:44:34.820
right now in the game?

00:44:34.820 --> 00:44:36.740
BRANDON BADGER: It's definitely
taking too long to

00:44:36.740 --> 00:44:38.260
approve portals.

00:44:38.260 --> 00:44:39.860
There's a couple things that
we're doing to improve that.

00:44:39.860 --> 00:44:43.340
One is we're building better
administration tools.

00:44:43.340 --> 00:44:48.120
So it was very primitive what
they were using before, but

00:44:48.120 --> 00:44:50.460
we're building some better back
end tools where they can

00:44:50.460 --> 00:44:53.460
see the photo of the submission,
they can quickly

00:44:53.460 --> 00:44:56.650
edit the data and approve
or reject it.

00:44:56.650 --> 00:44:59.090
So those tools, they're actually
much more productive

00:44:59.090 --> 00:45:00.180
with those tools.

00:45:00.180 --> 00:45:01.470
And then we're also hiring
out that team.

00:45:01.470 --> 00:45:05.520
I mean, there's different
strategies where maybe you

00:45:05.520 --> 00:45:07.770
could have fewer people review
items and whatnot.

00:45:07.770 --> 00:45:11.400
But we're trying to balance
the speed of approval with

00:45:11.400 --> 00:45:12.740
also quality.

00:45:12.740 --> 00:45:15.690
So I think we'll find a better
balance there where we can get

00:45:15.690 --> 00:45:17.370
them done a little faster, but
we don't want to start

00:45:17.370 --> 00:45:21.150
approving photos of a rock
in your backyard.

00:45:21.150 --> 00:45:25.030
We want it to really
still be art.

